text:
Anne Sweeny
Anne Sweeny was a high school crush of Dale Cooper.
Anne moved from Minnesota to Philadephia in 1969. On her first day, she introduced herself to Dale, who accidentally gave his name as "Ale."
Cooper had a crush on Anne for the rest of the school year. However, Anne became involved with Nancy Nordstrom, which prompted Dale to blow up Nancy's mailbox.
She soon moved back to the Great Plains, where her father had purchased a feed store. Cooper last saw her at a bookstore, purchasing a Willa Cather book for Nancy.
